headline: Adviseur Financial Control bij De Zorgcirkel
creator: False
bio:
Ik ben een ervaren financial op het gebied van Accounting en Controlling met een sterke hands-on mentaliteit.
Ik maak mijzelf snel zaken eigen en ben sterk in het leggen van verbanden en het aandragen van oplossingen en verbeteringen. Hiertoe zet ik op professionele wijze mijn organisatiesensitiviteit en projectvaardigheden in. 
Ik ben een open en gedreven teamplayer: een aanpakker met oog voor detail. 
Elke nieuwe uitdaging op financieel gebied pak ik enthousiast aan.

name: Frank Kwakman RA
headline: Senior Manager M&A Transaction Services | Registeraccountant |  Deloitte
creator: False
bio:
I started my professional career in 2014, when I joined the financial audit department of Deloitte. After 7 years as financial auditor I gained significant experience in accounting (Dutch GAAP, IFRS and US GAAP), internal controls and auditing, while also becoming a Dutch Certified Public Accountant (‘RA’). 

Since 2021 I’m working as a (senior) manager in the M&A Transaction Services team in Amsterdam, providing financial acquisition due diligence, vendor due diligence and refinancing due diligence services. I had the pleasure to serve on multiple landmark transactions, advising both national and international corporates as well as private equity firms. 

My industry focus is on industrial manufacturing and project-driven organisations, including construction and development, engineering, and particularly technical services. Some of the key clients I have been working for are VolkerWessels, BDR Thermea, Swegon, Unica, Van Wanrooij and multiple private equity firms. 

Besides my professional career at Deloitte, I am passionate about using my financial background to contribute to society. From 2020 to 2023, I volunteered as a board member (treasurer) of Football Club EVC, with around 500 members and 100 volunteers. In this role I was ultimately responsible for day-to-day activities and finance related matters, including budgeting, reporting, tax compliance and investment and sponsorship deals, as well as annual presentations to our members. As of 2024, I take a seat in the financial supervision committee.

name: Lonneke Korenromp
headline: Certified leadership coach and facilitator (CPCC, PCC, ORSC trained)  🔹 Head of Career Services and Alumni Relations VU School of Business and Economics 🔹 Lead from within
creator: False
past_company_1: VU School of Business and Economics
bio:
I’m an ICF-certified leadership coach (CPCC, PCC) with 25 years of experience in personal and professional development. I’ve worked as a psychologist, consultant, coach, and manager — and today I coach students, professionals and leaders who want to work, lead, and live in a way that feels more real and self-directed.

We are all leaders — in our own lives, careers, and environments. Each of us carries responsibility for the world we help shape. And yet, we live in a world where doing often takes over: achieving, pushing forward, ticking off to-do lists. But leadership isn’t just about what you do; it’s about who you are. In my coaching practice, Embrace your Impact, I support leaders in developing the 'being' side of leadership — creating space, reflecting deeply, and reconnecting with your core essence.

I work with professionals at all stages of their careers — from emerging leaders to seasoned executives. My coaching is rooted in inner work: uncovering the patterns that hold you back, understanding what drives your decisions, and learning to lead from within. This process creates space to listen into your inner wisdom, make resonant choices and lead in a way that aligns with who you really are. As a result, you'll move through complexity with more confidence, set clearer boundaries and feel more grounded and connected — to yourself and others.

Alongside individual coaching, I also work with groups through workshops and team coaching. These sessions offer powerful opportunities for collective insight and (re)connection within teams and organizations.

I believe that embracing every part of ourselves — our strengths, doubts, and contradictions — allows us to lead with intention, presence, and purpose. Reach out if you want to discover how this can elevate your leadership!

name: Ingmar Kappers
headline:
You run into a tough puzzle, together we solve this puzzle!

Master of Puzzles, organizational coach, change specialist, podcasthost
creator: True
bio:
👌Wat ik doe: 
ik help organisaties om het verschil te maken in lastige vraagstukken met project/programmamanagement, advies, training en begeleiding

🏆 Mijn kracht
- Samen tot de essentie van het vraagstuk komen
- De puzzel (samen) leggen en oplossen.

Anderen zeiden:
🗣️ 𝘐𝘯𝘨𝘮𝘢𝘳 𝘻𝘦𝘵 𝘻𝘰𝘸𝘦𝘭 𝘨𝘳𝘰𝘦𝘱𝘦𝘯 𝘢𝘭𝘴 𝘪𝘯𝘥𝘪𝘷𝘪𝘥𝘶𝘦𝘦𝘭 𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘴𝘦𝘯 𝘪𝘯 𝘣𝘦𝘸𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘨. 𝘏𝘪𝘫 𝘪𝘴 𝘥𝘶𝘪𝘥𝘦𝘭𝘪𝘫𝘬 𝘯𝘢𝘢𝘳 𝘻𝘪𝘫𝘯 𝘰𝘱𝘥𝘳𝘢𝘤𝘩𝘵𝘨𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘳 𝘦𝘯 𝘩𝘦𝘦𝘧𝘵 𝘯𝘪𝘦𝘵 𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘦𝘦𝘯 𝘰𝘰𝘨 𝘷𝘰𝘰𝘳 𝘦𝘦𝘯 𝘥𝘶𝘶𝘳𝘻𝘢𝘮𝘦 𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘦𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘮𝘢𝘢𝘳 𝘱𝘭𝘢𝘢𝘵𝘴 𝘥𝘢𝘵 𝘰𝘰𝘬 𝘪𝘯 𝘻𝘪𝘫𝘯 𝘣𝘦𝘦𝘭𝘥 𝘷𝘢𝘯 𝘥𝘦 𝘩𝘢𝘢𝘭𝘣𝘢𝘢𝘳𝘩𝘦𝘪𝘥 𝘷𝘢𝘯 𝘥𝘦 𝘨𝘦𝘸𝘦𝘯𝘴𝘵𝘦 𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘦𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘪𝘯 𝘦𝘦𝘯 𝘰𝘳𝘨𝘢𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘦, 𝘤.𝘲. 𝘥𝘦 𝘴𝘱𝘢𝘯𝘬𝘳𝘢𝘤𝘩𝘵 𝘷𝘢𝘯 𝘥𝘪𝘦 𝘰𝘳𝘨𝘢𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘦.'
-Jan Dirk Pruim gemeentesecretaris Gemeente Dronten

🗣️ 𝘐𝘯𝘨𝘮𝘢𝘳 𝘩𝘢𝘢𝘭 𝘫𝘦 𝘦𝘳𝘣𝘪𝘫 𝘢𝘭𝘴 𝘣𝘦𝘸𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘸𝘪𝘭 𝘤𝘳𝘦ë𝘳𝘦𝘯 𝘪𝘯 𝘫𝘦 𝘰𝘳𝘨𝘢𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘦. 𝘏𝘪𝘫 𝘪𝘴 𝘦𝘦𝘯 𝘵𝘺𝘱𝘦 ‘𝘤𝘰𝘯𝘴𝘪𝘨𝘭𝘪𝘦𝘳𝘦’ - 𝘪𝘯 𝘥𝘦 𝘨𝘰𝘦𝘥𝘦 𝘻𝘪𝘯 - 𝘸𝘢𝘢𝘳𝘮𝘦𝘦 𝘫𝘦 𝘪𝘯 𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘵𝘳𝘰𝘶𝘸𝘦𝘯 𝘢𝘢𝘯 𝘦𝘦𝘯 𝘯𝘪𝘦𝘶𝘸𝘦 𝘰𝘳𝘨𝘢𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘦 𝘸𝘪𝘭 𝘸𝘦𝘳𝘬𝘦𝘯. 𝘚𝘵𝘦𝘳𝘬 𝘢𝘭𝘴 𝘬𝘭𝘢𝘯𝘬𝘣𝘰𝘳𝘥, 𝘮𝘢𝘢𝘳 𝘰𝘰𝘬 𝘤𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘦𝘧 𝘪𝘯 𝘯𝘪𝘦𝘶𝘸𝘦 𝘷𝘰𝘳𝘮𝘦𝘯 𝘷𝘢𝘯 𝘸𝘦𝘳𝘬𝘦𝘯 𝘦𝘯 𝘩𝘦𝘵 𝘣𝘦𝘥𝘦𝘯𝘬𝘦𝘯 𝘷𝘢𝘯 𝘪𝘯𝘵𝘦𝘳𝘷𝘦𝘯𝘵𝘪𝘦𝘴. 𝘞𝘦𝘳𝘬𝘦𝘯 𝘮𝘦𝘵 𝘐𝘯𝘨𝘮𝘢𝘳 𝘣𝘦𝘵𝘦𝘬𝘦𝘯𝘵 𝘴𝘯𝘦𝘭𝘩𝘦𝘪𝘥, 𝘯𝘪𝘦𝘵 𝘭𝘶𝘭𝘭𝘦𝘯 𝘮𝘢𝘢𝘳 𝘱𝘰𝘦𝘵𝘴𝘦𝘯, 𝘴𝘤𝘩𝘦𝘳𝘱 𝘰𝘱 𝘥𝘦 𝘪𝘯𝘩𝘰𝘶𝘥, 𝘮𝘢𝘢𝘳 𝘷𝘰𝘰𝘳𝘢𝘭 𝘰𝘰𝘬 𝘧𝘪𝘫𝘯 𝘴𝘢𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘸𝘦𝘳𝘬𝘦𝘯.
-Jan Inberg, interim manager 

🗣️ 𝘐𝘯𝘨𝘮𝘢𝘳 𝘸𝘦𝘳𝘬𝘵 𝘩𝘪𝘫 𝘷𝘢𝘯𝘶𝘪𝘵 𝘥𝘪𝘦𝘱𝘦, 𝘥𝘰𝘰𝘳𝘭𝘦𝘦𝘧𝘥𝘦 𝘬𝘦𝘯𝘯𝘪𝘴 𝘦𝘯 𝘦𝘳𝘷𝘢𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘪𝘯 𝘥𝘪𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘴𝘦 𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘦𝘳𝘬𝘶𝘯𝘥𝘪𝘨𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘯𝘢𝘥𝘦𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘨𝘦𝘯. 𝘎𝘦𝘦𝘯 "𝘰𝘯𝘦 𝘴𝘪𝘻𝘦 𝘧𝘪𝘵𝘴 𝘢𝘭𝘭" 𝘮𝘢𝘢𝘳 𝘸𝘦𝘳𝘬𝘦𝘯 𝘷𝘢𝘯𝘶𝘪𝘵 𝘸𝘢𝘵 𝘦𝘳 𝘯𝘰𝘥𝘪𝘨 𝘪𝘴. 𝘐𝘬 𝘬𝘢𝘯 𝘐𝘯𝘨𝘮𝘢𝘳 𝘥𝘢𝘢𝘳𝘰𝘮 𝘷𝘢𝘯 𝘩𝘢𝘳𝘵𝘦 𝘢𝘢𝘯𝘣𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘭𝘦𝘯 𝘷𝘰𝘰𝘳 𝘤𝘰𝘮𝘱𝘭𝘦𝘹𝘦 𝘷𝘳𝘢𝘢𝘨𝘴𝘵𝘶𝘬𝘬𝘦𝘯 𝘸𝘢𝘢𝘳 𝘫𝘦 𝘦𝘦𝘯 𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘷𝘪𝘨𝘦 (𝘴𝘱𝘢𝘳𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘨𝘴)𝘱𝘢𝘳𝘵𝘯𝘦𝘳 𝘷𝘰𝘰𝘳 𝘻𝘰𝘦𝘬𝘵.
-Anton van der Vloet  Afdelingshoofd FAIR/VOR, Gemeente Amsterdam

✴️Mensen beschrijven me als:
- Slim en invoelend 
- Scherp met humor

Aan welke rollen kun je denken:  
- leiderschaps/organisatieontwikkeling
- sparringspartner directie en management

name: Horia Toma Pintilie
headline: Consultant | M&A Transaction Services at Deloitte
creator: False
bio: Young professional specialised in international M&A operations. Currently part of Deloitte Netherlands’ financial due diligence practice, I have successfully advised on multiple deals up to $3.3 billion by providing sell-side and buy-side financial due diligence, as well as assisting in the delivery of carve-out financials. Previous experience includes corporate finance, specifically enterprise valuations and the creation of Investment Memoranda.

name: Vincent Koops
headline: CX enthousiaste manager,Resultaatgericht/Analystisch/Verbinder
creator: False
current_position: Manager Operations customer journey’s Pilot “rode knop team”
bio:
“En hoe zal de klant dat ervaren? ” Die vraag hield mij niet alleen bezig toen ik zelf in de sales actief was maar ook later als leidinggevende en als CX deskundige. Het is de basis waarmee ik nu organisaties & (management)teams help de ambities op gebied van klantbeleving om te zetten in (klantgerichte) acties. 
Ik kom snel tot de kern, durf de status-quo te benoemen en uit te dagen, en help veranderingen te realiseren.
Dit doe ik op basis van mijn leidinggevende ervaring,  kennis van CX en verschillende management en projectmanagement methodieken, kennis op het gebied van psychologie, data management, en vooral door te zijn, wie ik ben. Ik bouw aan vertrouwen,denk vanuit de klant en in kansen.
